cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the intersection of cryptography and machine learning, specifically using homomorphic encryption to perform neural network predictions over encrypted data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also heavily involves neural networks, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with privacy concerns, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves data manipulation and analysis, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
